\begin{MintedVerbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
Task ID: ```\PYGZob{}task\PYGZus{}id\PYGZcb{}```

Real Context:
```\PYGZob{}context\PYGZcb{}```

Supporting Documents To Validate:
```\PYGZob{}supporting\PYGZus{}documents\PYGZcb{}```

You are validating whether the supporting documents for this single task are good enough for downstream use.

Important principle:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Judge the supporting documents collectively.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The goal is NOT perfection, but usability.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Minor phrasing or formatting differences are acceptable if the documents still cover the useful details from the real context.

Validation criteria:
\PYG{k}{1.} Coverage:
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Collectively, the supporting documents should contain all useful details from the real context.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Minor wording differences are acceptable if meaning is preserved.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Small omissions are acceptable only when they do not affect understanding or downstream usefulness.

\PYG{k}{2.} Source realism:
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The supporting documents should use appropriate source types and realistic presentation styles.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Metadata, tone, structure, and document format should feel plausible for the claimed source.

\PYG{k}{3.} Context alignment:
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The documents should stay aligned with the real context rather than drifting to a different scenario.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not treat clearly irrelevant extra content as acceptable.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }No conflicting information: the documents should not contain information that contradicts the real context. (wrong time period, wrong entity, wrong setting, etc.)
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If one supporting document presents itself as a final summary, final assessment, or precise forecast sequence for the target period, it should not omit a key transition that is part of the real context\PYGZsq{}s expected sequence; such omissions are major only when they make the document materially misleading rather than merely incomplete on its own.

\PYG{k}{4.} Temporal consistency:
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The supporting documents should be temporally consistent with the real context.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Dates, time windows, and relative time expressions should not point to a clearly different incident or period.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If a document describes a different date or time period while presenting it as the same immediate or current event, that is a major issue.

\PYG{k}{5.} Entity consistency:
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The supporting documents must stay consistent about the core entity or asset identity referenced by the real context.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If the real context refers to a specific terminal, unit, site, device, location, or named entity, the supporting documents should not switch to a different one unless the equivalence is explicitly clear.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Cross\PYGZhy{}document inconsistencies in terminal names, unit IDs, site names, or other core identifiers are major issues when they make the evidence set refer to different entities.

\PYG{k}{6.} Collective usefulness:
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The documents may divide information across multiple sources, but together they should still be easy to use.
\PYG{+w}{   }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Redundant overlap is acceptable if it improves clarity, but excessive redundancy that reduces usability is a problem.

Judgment rules:

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYGZdq{}correct\PYGZdq{}:
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }All 4 validation criteria are satisfied.
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Minor issues are allowed if they do NOT materially affect coverage, realism, or downstream usefulness.

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYGZdq{}needs\PYGZus{}correction\PYGZdq{}:
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }At least one major issue exists, including but not limited to:
\PYG{+w}{    }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }missing useful real\PYGZhy{}context details that affect understanding,
\PYG{+w}{    }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }inappropriate or unrealistic source types / presentation,
\PYG{+w}{    }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }documents that drift away from the real context,
\PYG{+w}{    }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }collectively unusable supporting coverage.
\PYG{+w}{    }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }documents that point to a clearly different date, time window, or incident period than the real context,
\PYG{+w}{    }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }conflicting terminal / unit / site / device / entity identifiers across supporting documents or against the real context,

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYGZdq{}uncertain\PYGZdq{}:
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The case is borderline and it is unclear whether the issues materially affect downstream usefulness.
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Use this sparingly; prefer \PYGZdq{}correct\PYGZdq{} if the supporting set is usable.

Severity guidelines:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }major: Affects coverage, realism, alignment, temporal consistency, entity consistency, or downstream usefulness.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }minor: Stylistic, formatting, or low\PYGZhy{}impact presentation issue.

Output formatting rules:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }When referring to a specific supporting document, always use the provided \PYG{l+s+sb}{`id`} field exactly as given, such as \PYG{l+s+sb}{`Supporting Document 04`}.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not invent shorthand forms like \PYG{l+s+sb}{`Doc 04`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`04/05`}, or other alternative labels.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If a finding concerns multiple documents, list each exact document id explicitly, for example \PYG{l+s+sb}{`Supporting Document 04; Supporting Document 05`}.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Keep the same exact document ids in \PYG{l+s+sb}{`target\PYGZus{}id`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`reason`}, and \PYG{l+s+sb}{`evidence`} whenever a finding is tied to specific documents.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }For every finding, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`repair\PYGZus{}target\PYGZus{}ids`} should list the exact provided document ids that should be regenerated to fix that issue.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Even when an issue is collective, map it to the concrete supporting document ids that should be repaired whenever possible instead of leaving it purely abstract.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`repair\PYGZus{}instruction`} must be concrete, edit\PYGZhy{}ready, and specific enough that applying it would resolve the full issue for the listed \PYG{l+s+sb}{`repair\PYGZus{}target\PYGZus{}ids`} without guesswork.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Across all findings, the repair instructions should collectively address all major issues in the supporting set.

Return valid JSON only with this schema, no other text:
\PYGZob{}
  \PYGZdq{}judge\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}correct | needs\PYGZus{}correction | uncertain\PYGZdq{},
  \PYGZdq{}confidence\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}high | medium | low\PYGZdq{},
  \PYGZdq{}summary\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}short overall judgment\PYGZdq{},
  \PYGZdq{}findings\PYGZdq{}: [
    \PYGZob{}
      \PYGZdq{}severity\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}major | minor\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}issue\PYGZus{}type\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}snake\PYGZus{}case\PYGZus{}issue\PYGZus{}type\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}target\PYGZus{}id\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}exact provided document id such as Supporting Document 04, or a precise collective label such as collective\PYGZus{}coverage or source\PYGZus{}realism\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}repair\PYGZus{}target\PYGZus{}ids\PYGZdq{}: [\PYGZdq{}Supporting Document 04\PYGZdq{}],
      \PYGZdq{}reason\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}short reason\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}evidence\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}short text span or explanation from the real context or supporting docs\PYGZdq{},
      \PYGZdq{}repair\PYGZus{}instruction\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}specific instruction that would fully resolve this issue for the listed repair\PYGZus{}target\PYGZus{}ids\PYGZdq{}
    \PYGZcb{}
  ],
  \PYGZdq{}correction\PYGZus{}hint\PYGZdq{}: \PYGZdq{}note for a human editor\PYGZdq{}
\PYGZcb{}
\end{MintedVerbatim}
